pull_request.title: Automatically check for SPDX headers and linting
Add bitinterleaved inplace Keccak implementation
pull_request.body:
Resolves #21 

This adds the bitinterleaved inplace Keccak implementation from https://github.com/XKCP/XKCP/blob/master/lib/low/KeccakP-1600/plain-32bits-inplace/KeccakP-1600-inplace32BI.c. 

We are approximately 200 bytes off the state of the art now (https://github.com/mupq/pqm4/blob/master/benchmarks.md)

| scheme      | stack keygen | stack encaps | stack decaps  |
| -----------------| ------------------- | ------------------- | ------------------- |
|mlkem512   | 2468 | 2524 |2524
|mlkem768   | 2980 | 3036 | 3036 
|mlkem1024 | 3492 | 3548 | 3548

Speed is also improved, but we are still rather far from the state of the art. 

Unfortunately this implementation is also CC0-licensed, so we'll have to either replace it later with our own Apache-2.0 implementation or check with the Keccak time if they'd be willing to re-license.
